The paper proposes a neural network encoder for time series data that can be adapted to new data types. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to machine learning and data analysis. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a neural network encoder for time series data, which is a common topic in machine learning research. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method for learning representations that can be adapted to new data types, which is a common goal in artificial intelligence research. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper uses a convolutional neural network, which is a common type of network used in computer vision research. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a neural network encoder, which is a topic related to neural computing. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper uses a convolutional attention mechanism to summarize the temporal output of the network, which is a technique that has been used in natural language processing research.
